text: Janville-en-Beauce is a commune in the Eure-et-Loir department in northern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Janville (the seat), Allaines-Mervilliers and Le Puiset.Arrêté préfectoral 19 December 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Eure-et-Loir department ==References== Category:Communes of Eure-et-Loir
title: Janville-en-Beauce
